**PATENT CLAIMS**

1. **(Independent – Amended)**  
   An operating method of a function approximation unit configured to approximate a nonlinear function within a neural processing unit, the function approximation unit comprising:  
   an input register;  
   a plurality of preprocessing circuits respectively dedicated to different nonlinear functions and configured to perform a function‑specific preprocessing selected from the group consisting of a reciprocal function, a reciprocal of a square‑root function, and a negative exponential function;  
   a single shared programmable function approximation circuit configured to approximate only a mantissa component using a comparator‑based segmentation scheme;  
   a plurality of post‑processing circuits respectively paired with the plurality of preprocessing circuits and configured to perform a function‑specific post‑processing;  
   a control‑signal generator that produces a two‑bit control signal;  
   a multiplexer that routes the input value from the input register to a selected one of the plurality of preprocessing circuits in response to the two‑bit control signal;  
   an intermediate register that stores the preprocessing result generated by the selected preprocessing circuit;  
   a demultiplexer that routes the preprocessing result and the approximated function output from the single shared programmable function approximation circuit to a selected one of the plurality of post‑processing circuits in response to a second two‑bit control signal; and  
   an output register that stores a final output value from the selected post‑processing circuit;  
   the method comprising:  
   storing an input value in the input register;  
   generating the two‑bit control signal;  
   routing the input value to a selected preprocessing circuit using the multiplexer;  
   generating a preprocessing result in the selected preprocessing circuit;  
   storing the preprocessing result in the intermediate register;  
   transmitting the preprocessing result to the single shared programmable function approximation circuit;  
   approximating only a mantissa component of the nonlinear function in the single shared programmable function approximation circuit using a comparator‑based segmentation scheme;  
   generating an approximated function output in the single shared programmable function approximation circuit;  
   routing the approximated function output and the preprocessing result to a selected post‑processing circuit using the demultiplexer;  
   post‑processing the approximated function output or the preprocessing result in the selected post‑processing circuit; and  
   storing the final output value in the output register.  

2. **(Dependent – Amended)**  
   The operating method of claim 1, wherein the two‑bit control signal comprises a first bit that selects one of the plurality of preprocessing circuits and a second bit that selects one of the plurality of post‑processing circuits.  

3. **(Dependent – Amended)**  
   The operating method of claim 1, wherein the comparator‑based segmentation scheme comprises a plurality of comparators that compare the preprocessing result against a set of reference thresholds and generate segmentation signals that define segmentation intervals for the mantissa component.  

4. **(Dependent – Amended)**  
   The operating method of claim 1, wherein the single shared programmable function approximation circuit comprises a lookup‑table storing a plurality of approximation coefficients and a micro‑controller that selects a coefficient based on the segmentation signals and computes the approximated mantissa component using a polynomial evaluation.  

5. **(Dependent – Amended)**  
   The operating method of claim 1, wherein the post‑processing circuit for the reciprocal function implements a reciprocal approximation using a Newton‑Raphson iteration, and wherein the post‑processing circuit for the reciprocal of a square‑root function implements a square‑root approximation using a binary‑search algorithm.  

6. **(Dependent – Amended)**  
   The operating method of claim 1, wherein the function‑specific post‑processing includes an exponent conversion that adjusts the exponent of the approximated function output before concatenation with the mantissa component.  

7. **(Dependent – Original – Amended)**  
   The operating method of claim 1, wherein each of the plurality of preprocessing circuits comprises a first decomposition circuit, a first decoder, and an input‑value generation circuit that together implement the function‑specific preprocessing for the reciprocal, reciprocal‑square‑root, or negative exponential function.  

8. **(Dependent – Original – Amended)**  
   The operating method of claim 1, wherein each of the plurality of post‑processing circuits comprises an exponent conversion circuit, a second decomposition circuit, a second decoder, an adder, an encoder, and a concatenation circuit that together implement the function‑specific post‑processing for the reciprocal, reciprocal‑square‑root, or negative exponential function.  

9. **(Dependent – Original – Amended)**  
   The operating method of claim 1, wherein the plurality of preprocessing circuits and the plurality of post‑processing circuits are variably configured according to a function type selected from the group consisting of reciprocal, reciprocal‑square‑root, and negative exponential.  

10. **(Dependent – Original – Amended)**  
    The operating method of claim 1, wherein the final output value is transmitted to the output register through the demultiplexer and stored therein.  

